abstract: Riot police clashed with protesters in the streets Wednesday night outside a soccer match between Barcelona and Real Madrid, as authorities sought to keep Catalonia's separatist movement from disrupting the game viewed by 650 million people worldwide.
snippet: Riot police clashed with protesters in the streets Wednesday night outside a soccer match between Barcelona and Real Madrid, as authorities sought to keep Catalonia's separatist movement from disrupting the game viewed by 650 million people worldw...
lead_paragraph: BARCELONA, Spain — Riot police clashed with protesters in the streets Wednesday night outside a soccer match between Barcelona and Real Madrid, as authorities sought to keep Catalonia's separatist movement from disrupting the game viewed by 650 million people worldwide.
headline_main: Police, Protesters Clash Outside Barcelona-Real Madrid Game
headline_print_headline: Police, Protesters Clash Outside Barcelona-Real Madrid Game

abstract: Slovakia's Constitutional Court on Wednesday suspended a law putting in place one of the world's longest bans on publishing opinion polls before elections, preventing the bill from taking effect before a parliamentary vote in February.
snippet: Slovakia's Constitutional Court on Wednesday suspended a law putting in place one of the world's longest bans on publishing opinion polls before elections, preventing the bill from taking effect before a parliamentary vote in February.
lead_paragraph: PRAGUE — Slovakia's Constitutional Court on Wednesday suspended a law putting in place one of the world's longest bans on publishing opinion polls before elections, preventing the bill from taking effect before a parliamentary vote in February.
headline_main: Slovak Court Suspends Bill for Europe's Longest Pre-election Poll Blackout
headline_print_headline: Slovak Court Suspends Bill for Europe's Longest Pre-election Poll Blackout

abstract: The Democratic-controlled U.S. House of Representatives will vote on Wednesday to formally charge President Donald Trump, a Republican, with "high crimes and misdemeanors," making him only the third U.S. president in history to be impeached.
snippet: The Democratic-controlled U.S. House of Representatives will vote on Wednesday to formally charge President Donald Trump, a Republican, with "high crimes and misdemeanors," making him only the third U.S. president in history to be impeached.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Democratic-controlled U.S. House of Representatives will vote on Wednesday to formally charge President Donald Trump, a Republican, with "high crimes and misdemeanors," making him only the third U.S. president in history to be impeached.
headline_main: Explainer: The Case for Trump's Impeachment-And the Case Against It

abstract: Chancellor Angela Merkel on Wednesday defended Germany's voting record on Israel at the United Nations, arguing that supporting the country doesn't mean backing all of its actions.
snippet: Chancellor Angela Merkel on Wednesday defended Germany's voting record on Israel at the United Nations, arguing that supporting the country doesn't mean backing all of its actions.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — Chancellor Angela Merkel on Wednesday defended Germany's voting record on Israel at the United Nations, arguing that supporting the country doesn't mean backing all of its actions.
headline_main: Merkel Defends Germany's UN Voting Record on Israel
headline_print_headline: Merkel Defends Germany's UN Voting Record on Israel

abstract: The decision was a setback to efforts by a district attorney to ensure Mr. Manafort would still face prison time if President Trump pardoned him.
snippet: The decision was a setback to efforts by a district attorney to ensure Mr. Manafort would still face prison time if President Trump pardoned him.
lead_paragraph: A New York judge on Wednesday threw out state fraud charges against Paul J. Manafort, President Trump’s former campaign chairman, dealing a setback to efforts by the Manhattan district attorney to ensure Mr. Manafort would still face prosecution should Mr. Trump pardon him for his federal crimes.

headline_main: State Charges Against Manafort Dismissed by Judge in New York
headline_print_headline: Double Jeopardy Law  Ends Manafort Case

abstract: A New York judge threw out state mortgage fraud charges against Paul Manafort, ruling Wednesday that the criminal case was too similar to one that has already landed President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman in federal prison.
snippet: A New York judge threw out state mortgage fraud charges against Paul Manafort, ruling Wednesday that the criminal case was too similar to one that has already landed President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman in federal prison.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A New York judge threw out state mortgage fraud charges against Paul Manafort, ruling Wednesday that the criminal case was too similar to one that has already landed President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman in federal prison.

abstract: Love it or hate it, Andrew Lloyd Webber’s musical is one of the most popular of all time. Before the new movie adaptation comes out, catch up on its four-decade history.
snippet: Love it or hate it, Andrew Lloyd Webber’s musical is one of the most popular of all time. Before the new movie adaptation comes out, catch up on its four-decade history.
lead_paragraph: The first trailer for “Cats” — you know which one I’m talking about — is far from the first time the Andrew Lloyd Webber musical has attracted a wide range of extreme responses: horror, confusion, deranged confusion and, perhaps, bright-eyed excitement.

lead_paragraph: RIO DE JANEIRO — Rio de Janeiro state prosecutors on Wednesday raided properties of the former staff of Flavio Bolsonaro, the son of Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro, and relatives of the president's ex-wife, according to prosecutors and two sources familiar with the matter.

abstract: Paul Manafort, U.S. President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman, on Wednesday won the dismissal of New York state fraud charges, in a defeat for the Manhattan district attorney's efforts to hold him accountable even if pardoned by Trump.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Paul Manafort, U.S. President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman, on Wednesday won the dismissal of New York state fraud charges, in a defeat for the Manhattan district attorney's efforts to hold him accountable even if pardoned by Trump.

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives began debate on Wednesday ahead of a historic vote on two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump, who is poised to become the nation's third president to be impeached.
